    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#gpc1961"/> pp. 45-47, n. <citedRange>26</citedRange> (ph.)</bibl> (from †Oliverio's papers; with note by Pugliese Carratelli), whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>20.756</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdl1970"/>, pp. 248-249, n. <citedRange>19</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2000"/> pp. <citedRange>216, 231</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>50.1637</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>003300</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#parisipresicce2007"/>, p. 249, n. <citedRange>18</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>57.2001</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                    
                <div type="textpart" subtype="compartment" n="a">
                    <ab>
                        <lb n="1" xml:id="l1"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Karneios"><name nymRef="#Καρνῆιος"><expan><abbr>Καρ</abbr><ex cert="high">νείο̄</ex></expan></name></persName>                    
                    </ab>
                </div>
               
                <div type="textpart" subtype="compartment" n="b">
                    <ab>
                        <lb corresp="#l1"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Opheles"><name nymRef="#Ὀφέλης"><expan><abbr>Ὀφ</abbr><ex cert="high">έλευς</ex></expan></name></persName>                    
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                <app loc="a1+b1">
                    <lem resp="#cdl2000"><expan><abbr>Καρ</abbr><ex cert="high">νειο̄</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Ὀφ</abbr><ex cert="high">έλευς</ex></expan></lem> 
                    <rdg resp="#gpc1961 #parisipresicce2007">Καρόφι <note>both following †Oliverio</note></rdg>
                </app>
                </p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
                <p>a) <supplied reason="subaudible">Autel</supplied> de <expan><abbr>Kar</abbr><ex>neios</ex></expan>.</p>
                <p> b) <supplied reason="subaudible">Autel</supplied> d'<expan><abbr>Oph</abbr><ex>eles</ex></expan>.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
                <p>a) <supplied reason="subaudible">Altar</supplied> of <expan><abbr>Kar</abbr><ex>neios</ex></expan>.</p>
                <p> b) <supplied reason="subaudible">Altar</supplied> of <expan><abbr>Oph</abbr><ex>eles</ex></expan>.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
                <p>a) <supplied reason="subaudible">Altare</supplied> di <expan><abbr>Kar</abbr><ex>neios</ex></expan>.</p>
                <p> b) <supplied reason="subaudible">Altare</supplied> di <expan><abbr>Oph</abbr><ex>eles</ex></expan>.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>About the circumstances of the discovery, see <bibl><ptr target="#sillani2014"/>, p. <citedRange>104</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
                <p>Oliverio's reading as one word <foreign xml:lang="grc">Καροφι</foreign> is questionable for the extreme scarcity of plural datives in <foreign xml:lang="grc">-φι</foreign> and mainly because a divine name *<foreign xml:lang="grc">κᾶρες</foreign>
                    (or rather *<foreign xml:lang="grc">κᾶροι</foreign>) does not exist. Two abbreviated names, each 
                    corresponding to one compartment would be a better solution. The vertical stroke at the right end does not seem to be a iota, but a limit 
                    for the inscribed field.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
